sequenceDiagram
    participant Client as External Client
    participant API as Apiserver<br/>HTTP/HTTPS
    participant PG as PostgreSQL<br/>5432/TCP
    participant Redis as Redis/Valkey<br/>6379/TCP
    participant FS as File Store<br/>(S3/Filesystem)
    participant Proc as Processor<br/>(Worker Pool)
    participant LLM as Inference Gateway<br/>(llm-d / vLLM)
    participant GC as Batch GC

    rect rgb(230, 245, 255)
        Note over Client,FS: Flow 1: Batch Job Submission & Execution
        Client->>API: POST /v1/files (multipart JSONL)<br/>Header: X-MaaS-Username
        API->>API: Validate (max 200MB, 50K lines)<br/>LimitedCountingReader
        API->>FS: Upload file content<br/>HTTPS/443 (S3) or local
        API->>PG: Store file metadata<br/>TCP/5432 TLS
        API-->>Client: 200 File object (file_id)

        Client->>API: POST /v1/batches<br/>Header: X-MaaS-Username
        API->>PG: Create batch record<br/>TCP/5432 TLS
        API->>Redis: Enqueue to priority queue<br/>(sorted set, SLO priority)<br/>TCP/6379 TLS
        API-->>Client: 200 Batch object (batch_id, status=validating)

        Proc->>Redis: BLMPop dequeue job<br/>(semaphore-driven polling)
        Redis-->>Proc: Job payload
        Proc->>FS: Download input JSONL<br/>HTTPS/443
        Proc->>Redis: Update status: in_progress

        loop For each line in JSONL (concurrency-controlled)
            Proc->>LLM: POST inference request<br/>Bearer token auth<br/>HTTP/HTTPS TLS 1.2+
            LLM-->>Proc: Inference response
            Proc->>Redis: Update progress counter
        end

        Proc->>FS: Upload output JSONL<br/>HTTPS/443
        Proc->>FS: Upload error JSONL (if errors)<br/>HTTPS/443
        Proc->>PG: Update batch: completed<br/>TCP/5432
        Proc->>Redis: Final status update
    end

    rect rgb(255, 245, 230)
        Note over Client,Redis: Flow 2: Batch Cancellation
        Client->>API: POST /v1/batches/{id}/cancel<br/>Header: X-MaaS-Username
        API->>Redis: Publish cancel event<br/>(list-based event channel)
        API-->>Client: 200 Batch (status=cancelling)
        Redis-->>Proc: Cancel event received<br/>(BLMPop listener)
        Proc->>Proc: Cancel in-flight requests<br/>(context cancellation)
        Proc->>FS: Upload partial output
        Proc->>PG: Update batch: cancelled
    end

    rect rgb(245, 255, 230)
        Note over GC,FS: Flow 3: Garbage Collection
        loop Periodic (configurable interval)
            GC->>PG: Query expired batches/files<br/>TCP/5432
            PG-->>GC: Expired records
            GC->>FS: Delete expired file content<br/>HTTPS/443
            GC->>PG: Delete expired metadata
        end
    end
